---
description: AI Repo Companion runtime rules for Cursor.
alwaysApply: true
---

This repository is the hidden `.ai-repo-companion/` runtime that gets embedded inside a host project.

Working rules:

- keep edits grounded in the current runtime architecture
- prefer changing `src/lib/`, `config/`, `docs/`, and `tests/`
- do not hand-edit `state/` unless the task is explicitly about runtime state or fixtures
- keep new behavior visible through `status`, `report`, `run`, or smoke coverage

Host integration:

- use `npm run integrate -- --editor both` to generate host-facing Codex and Cursor instructions
- use `npm run integrate -- --editor both --hostRoot .. --writeHostFiles` to write those files into the parent host repo
- see `docs/HOST-INTEGRATION.md` before changing blind-deployment behavior

Runtime expectations:

- keep `provider-runtime` model-agnostic
- keep native Codex and Cursor paths working
- preserve stable stdin/stdout JSON contracts for command adapters
- if grounding is missing, block the run instead of inventing targets
